      • getAllAliases

        public Set<String> getAllAliases()
        Description copied from interface: CommandMapping
        Gets an immutable list of all aliases.

        The returned list must contain at least one entry, of which one must be the one returned by CommandMapping.getPrimaryAlias().

        There may be several versions of the same alias with different casing, although generally implementations should ignore the casing of aliases.

        Specified by:
        getAllAliases in interface CommandMapping
        Returns:
        A set of aliases
